 {"id":"beads_rust-1jcq","title":"Implement syntax highlighting for code blocks","description":"## Feature: Code Syntax Highlighting

### Purpose
When issue descriptions or comments contain code blocks, render them with syntax highlighting for improved readability.

### File Location
`src/format/syntax.rs`

### CRITICAL: Mode Behavior
Syntax highlighting ONLY in Rich mode:
- Rich: Full color syntax highlighting
- Plain: Code block with no colors (indented or fenced)
- JSON: Raw code string unchanged
- Quiet: No output

### Implementation

```rust
use rich_rust::syntax::Syntax;
use crate::format::OutputContext;

pub fn highlight_code(code: &str, language: &str, ctx: &OutputContext) -> String {
    if !ctx.is_rich() {
        // Plain mode: return indented code block
        return code.lines()
            .map(|l| format!("    {}", l))
            .collect::<Vec<_>>()
            .join("\n");
    }

    let syntax = Syntax::new(code, language)
        .with_line_numbers(code.lines().count() > 5)
        .with_theme("monokai")
        .with_word_wrap(ctx.width());

    syntax.render()
}
```

### Language Detection
1. Explicit fencing: ```rust
2. Filename hint: `main.rs`
3. Heuristics for common patterns
4. Default to "text" if unknown

### Supported Languages (Priority Order)
- rust, go, python, typescript, javascript
- sql, bash, yaml, json, toml
- html, css, markdown
- Others via syntect

---

## Testing Requirements

### Unit Tests
Location: tests/format/syntax_tests.rs

```rust
use beads_rust::format::syntax::highlight_code;
use beads_rust::format::OutputContext;

#[test]
fn test_highlight_rust() {
    let ctx = OutputContext::rich();
    let code = "fn main() { println!(\"Hello\"); }";
    let output = highlight_code(code, "rust", &ctx);
    assert!(output.contains("fn"));
    assert!(output.contains("main"));
}

#[test]
fn test_highlight_python() {
    let ctx = OutputContext::rich();
    let code = "def main():\n    print('Hello')";
    let output = highlight_code(code, "python", &ctx);
    assert!(output.contains("def"));
}

#[test]
fn test_highlight_plain_mode_no_colors() {
    let ctx = OutputContext::plain();
    let code = "fn main() {}";
    let output = highlight_code(code, "rust", &ctx);
    assert!(!contains_ansi_codes(&output));
    // Should be indented
    assert!(output.starts_with("    "));
}

#[test]
fn test_highlight_json_mode_unchanged() {
    let ctx = OutputContext::json();
    let code = "fn main() {}";
    let output = highlight_code(code, "rust", &ctx);
    assert_eq!(output, code);
}

#[test]
fn test_highlight_unknown_language() {
    let ctx = OutputContext::rich();
    let code = "some random text";
    let output = highlight_code(code, "unknown-lang", &ctx);
    // Should not crash, render as plain text
    assert!(output.contains("some random text"));
}

#[test]
fn test_highlight_line_numbers_for_long_code() {
    let ctx = OutputContext::rich();
    let code = (0..10).map(|i| format!("line {}", i)).collect::<Vec<_>>().join("\n");
    let output = highlight_code(&code, "text", &ctx);
    // Should have line numbers for >5 lines
    assert!(output.contains("1") || output.contains("│"));
}

#[test]
fn test_highlight_empty_code() {
    let ctx = OutputContext::rich();
    let output = highlight_code("", "rust", &ctx);
    assert!(output.is_empty() || output.trim().is_empty());
}

#[test]
fn test_language_detection_from_fence() {
    // When parsing markdown, should detect language
    let fence = "```rust\nfn main() {}\n```";
    let (lang, code) = parse_code_fence(fence);
    assert_eq!(lang, "rust");
}
